                                                    <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0;">Many people told me when I first started graduate school that there would be a lot of failures. It didn’t really sink in, but now, two and a half years in, I can say that there are a lot of failures. Failed experiments, paper rejections, that kind of stuff. But you learn, and it’s a very nice experience in a way – an oxymoron. But you become more resilient with each failure. And trying new things in the same research area, I’ve gained more experience and practical knowledge that helps things progress faster. </p>
