                                        <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0;">Though learning about Ravi’s project on decommissioning, I realize that there are many decommissioning scenarios and nuances with each of these scenarios. I realized that this is part of IoT research. I had previously thought of decommissioning in the general sense, but Ravi’s project highlights edge cases that I never considered but are important. </p>
                                        <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0;">And I wasn’t very familiar with the topic of privacy prior to my work on SPLICE. I could see the privacy problem, but reading Nathan’s paper, <a href="https://www.computer.org/csdl/proceedings-article/sp/2023/933600c112/1Js0EECmM2k"> “Optimistic Access Control for the Smart Home”</a> I realized there’s a whole sequence of events that I hadn’t previously considered. The smart-home is a very complex system, and in any complex system you’ll have interactions that the model you envision doesn’t encapsulate.</p>
